---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro'
import { site } from '../data/site'
---

<Base title="About" description={site.description}>
  <section class="head">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal">
        <SectionHeading
          eyebrow="About"
          title="A summit, and its open archive"
          lede="MedAI Summit is a yearly event on artificial intelligence in medicine. This site keeps its record, open to anyone."
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section pt-0">
    <div class="container layout">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <p>
          MedAI Summit is an annual summit on artificial intelligence in medicine. Each year we bring
          clinicians, researchers and engineers together to look at what AI can and cannot do in real
          clinical work, from radiology and cardiology to dentistry, oncology and the ethics of
          medical data. The people in the room are the people doing the work: radiologists reading
          real scans, cardiologists building early-detection tools, and engineers shipping products
          used by patients.
        </p>
        <p>
          The first edition ran online on 30 and 31 October 2025. More than 500 people from Iran,
          Colombia, India and Tajikistan joined 16 talks and workshops across the two days, close to
          9,000 person-hours of attention. Speakers came from Mayo Clinic, the World Health
          Organization, the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai, Tehran University of Medical
          Sciences and other institutions across Iran.
        </p>
        <p>
          This website is the archive, and only the archive. It holds past editions and grows by one
          entry a year. Every session from every edition was recorded, subtitled in English and
          shared with handouts, and it all stays available. If you missed a year, or want to send a
          colleague a specific talk, it is here.
        </p>
        <p>
          Registration, accounts and anything to do with the live event live on the main summit site,
          which is separate. There is no backend here and nothing to sign up for. The community
          carries on between editions on Telegram, and recordings are shared through the admin.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="panel reveal">
        <h2>Reach the summit</h2>
        <ul class="links">
          {
            site.socials.map((s) => (
              <li>
                <a href={s.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                  <span>{s.label}</span>
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="15" height="15" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M7 17 17 7M9 7h8v8" /></svg>
                </a>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
        <a href={site.contact} class="btn btn-primary panel-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Message the team</a>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section pt-0">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="invite-note reveal">
        <div class="invite-note-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Invited to speak?</p>
          <h2 class="invite-note-title">Present once, and it keeps reaching clinicians.</h2>
          <p class="invite-note-text">
            Every talk is recorded, subtitled in English and kept on this archive, in front of an
            audience that is mostly clinicians. If you have been invited, or want to be, the team is
            one message away.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href={site.contact} class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Message the team
          <svg class="arrow" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="17" height="17" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6" /></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .head {
    padding-block: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem) 1rem;
  }
  .pt-0 {
    padding-top: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }
  .prose p {
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .prose p + p {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
  }
  .prose p :global(strong) {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .panel {
    align-self: start;
    padding: 1.6rem;
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }
  .panel h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  .links {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .links a {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 0.7rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .links a:hover {
    color: var(--pine);
  }
  .panel-cta {
    width: 100%;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
  }
  .invite-note {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.6rem;
    padding: clamp(1.7rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }
  .invite-note-title {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.1rem);
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .invite-note-text {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .invite-note .btn {
    align-self: start;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1.7fr 1fr;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
    .invite-note {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 3rem;
    }
    .invite-note .btn {
      align-self: center;
    }
  }
</style>
